article.headline: Stony Brook 70, Hartford 62
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. (AP) -- Mike Popoko scored 15 points and Stony Brook snapped a six-game losing streak with a 70-62 victory over Hartford on Saturday. Cori Spencer added 13 points for the Seawolves (7-16, 4-10 America East, while Hendrik Feist had 12 on 4-for-4 shooting from 3-point range. Stony Brook, which had lost eight of nine, was 8-for-12 from 3-point range. Ryan Stys was 10-of-16 from the field and had 23 points for the Hawks (9-13, 4-9). Charles Ford had 13 points for Hartford and Aaron Cook added 12, all on 3-pointers. Cook had three 3-pointers as Hartford went on an 11-5 run over the final 5:11 of the first half to take a 36-26 lead. A 3 by Feist gave Stony Brook its first lead of the game, 50-49, with 7:37 to play. The Hawks tied it at 54 on a free throw by Ford with 5:04 left. A layup by Spencer started Stony Brook's 16-8 run that closed out the game. Popoko had five points in the run, three from the foul line.
